history.content: No. No other times will be available.  You might think of taking EE375 which would also meet your requirement although be less focused on the specifics of cs instruction. (And making plans hoping the actual evidence in front of you will turn out not to be true is often less successful than other models of problem-solving.)

I'm gonna be a first-time TA next semester, so I have to take CS375, and on the class search page, the only thing I saw for CS375 was 001-Dis on Monday 4-5 pm. I already enrolled in phase 1 for EE16A lab Monday 2-5 pm, so would I have to switch into another lab (and would I lost my spot in the class if I tried to do this). I know we are supposed to sign up for 375 sometime mid-August, but I wasn't sure if other times would be available.
history.subject: CS375 Conflict with Already Enrolled Class
